BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:2Y2xukXy9zs7rK5-8Hwze
SUMMARY:TADAIMA: I'm Home
DTSTAMP:20260214T003617Z
DTSTART:20260214T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:After more than 80 years\, a treasured collection returns “home
	” to Seattle’s Japanese American community. In 1942 dozens of traditional 
	Boys’ and Girls’ Day dolls were entrusted to Bailey Gatzert Elementary Sch
	ool by Japanese American families facing forced incarceration. Most were n
	ever reclaimed after the war. Artist Miya Sukune uses recent research in M
	OHAI’s collection\, as well as interviews with Japanese American survivors
	 and their descendants\, to create an installation called “Tadaima\,” mean
	ing “I’m home.”\n\nTADAIMA: “I’m Home!” Bringing Seattle’s Girls’ and Boys
	’ Day Dolls Home reconnects the dolls with their traditional role of prote
	cting and blessing children. It invites visitors to celebrate the resilien
	ce\, memory\, and enduring traditions of the Japanese American Community.\
	n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-02-14T00
LOCATION:Museum of History and Industry\, 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, Seatt
	le\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bGu56ehbAcOls-qRvppxV
SUMMARY:Collection Spotlight Exhibit
DTSTAMP:20260214T003617Z
DTSTART:20260214T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Saturday\, February 14\, 2026\, 10am - 6pm\n\nThis exhibit high
	lights the diversity and depth of The Seattle Public Library's collection\
	, composed of over two million items.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Library
	\n\nRoom Location: Level 8 - Gallery\n\nRegistration Required: Registratio
	n is not required.\n\nDetailed Description: Enjoy viewing books\, ephemera
	\, art\, and more at our exhibit in the Level 8 Gallery between January 23
	\, 2026 and April 11\, 2026.\, Thanks to our sponsor\n\nThe Seattle Public
	 Library Foundation .\n\nEvent Logistics:\n\nFind out about Exhibits.\n\nC
	ontact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 2
	06-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for peop
	le with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least 
	seven days before the event to request accommodations.\, All Library progr
	ams are free and open to the public.\,\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/collection-spotlight-exhi
	bit/18084351/2026-02-14T00
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT8H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:EKqzTSFZzLl8NKyouOMFX
SUMMARY:Toddler Play Group
DTSTAMP:20260214T003617Z
DTSTART:20260214T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Saturday\, February 14\, 2026\, 10am - 1pm\n\nA drop-in play gr
	oup for toddlers and their families.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nBallard Branch\n
	\nRoom Location: Meeting Room\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is no
	t required.\n\nDetailed Description: Early Learning is a great way for tod
	dlers and their families to develop learning\, literacy\, and language ski
	lls as well as community with other families.\, We play with toys\, share 
	books\, socialize\, and have engaging\, educational activities that help k
	ids and their caregivers grow together.\n\nEvent Logistics: Registration i
	s not required but these programs are very popular and the room capacity c
	an fill up quickly.\, Families of all ages are welcome\, though this early
	 learning program is intended for youth aged 1-3\, their caregivers and fa
	milies.\, Find out more about\n\nEarly Learning & Story Time\n\nprograms.\
	n\nContact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor ca
	ll 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for 
	people with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat le
	ast seven days before the event to request accommodations.\, All Library p
	rograms are free and open to the public.\,\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Cultu
	re
