BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:iPOply5lALOm34PD-BVDR
SUMMARY:TADAIMA: I'm Home
DTSTAMP:20260214T003617Z
DTSTART:20260215T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:After more than 80 years\, a treasured collection returns “home
	” to Seattle’s Japanese American community. In 1942 dozens of traditional 
	Boys’ and Girls’ Day dolls were entrusted to Bailey Gatzert Elementary Sch
	ool by Japanese American families facing forced incarceration. Most were n
	ever reclaimed after the war. Artist Miya Sukune uses recent research in M
	OHAI’s collection\, as well as interviews with Japanese American survivors
	 and their descendants\, to create an installation called “Tadaima\,” mean
	ing “I’m home.”\n\nTADAIMA: “I’m Home!” Bringing Seattle’s Girls’ and Boys
	’ Day Dolls Home reconnects the dolls with their traditional role of prote
	cting and blessing children. It invites visitors to celebrate the resilien
	ce\, memory\, and enduring traditions of the Japanese American Community.\
	n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-02-15T00
LOCATION:Museum of History and Industry\, 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, Seatt
	le\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3LcmfdgIOmJv3HwExpysA
SUMMARY:Collection Spotlight Exhibit
DTSTAMP:20260214T003617Z
DTSTART:20260215T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Sunday\, February 15\, 2026\, 10am - 6pm\n\nThis exhibit highli
	ghts the diversity and depth of The Seattle Public Library's collection\, 
	composed of over two million items.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n
	\nRoom Location: Level 8 - Gallery\n\nRegistration Required: Registration 
	is not required.\n\nDetailed Description: Enjoy viewing books\, ephemera\,
	 art\, and more at our exhibit in the Level 8 Gallery between January 23\,
	 2026 and April 11\, 2026.\, Thanks to our sponsor\n\nThe Seattle Public L
	ibrary Foundation .\n\nEvent Logistics:\n\nFind out about Exhibits.\n\nCon
	tact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206
	-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for people
	 with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least se
	ven days before the event to request accommodations.\, All Library program
	s are free and open to the public.\,\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
