UID:aap5Vp3J1HBAjUt4dbbPK
SUMMARY:NITE WAVE performs Prince & The Revolution's "Purple Rain" album in
	 full! + Everything She Wants (Wham/George Michael Tribute)
DTSTAMP:20260214T003618Z
DTSTART:20260221T040000Z
DESCRIPTION:Purple Rain is the sixth studio album by American recording art
	ist Prince\, the first to feature his band the Revolution\, and is the sou
	ndtrack to the 1984 film of the same name. It was released on June 25\, 19
	84 by Warner Bros. Records. The first two singles from the album\, When Do
	ves Cry and Lets Go Crazy\, topped the US singles charts\, and were hits a
	round the world\, while the title track went to number two on the Billboar
	d Hot 100. The album was certified thirteen-times platinum (diamond) by th
	e RIAA. As of 2008\, it has sold over 25 million copies worldwide\, making
	 it the third-best-selling soundtrack album of all time. Nite Wave - Seatt
	le\, WA - (NiteWaveParty.com). Known for their high energy show\, Nite Wav
	e continues their 80s dance ways performing New Wave hits from Duran Duran
	\, INXS\, Frankie Goes to Hollywood\, The Cure\, New Order\, Prince\, Depe
	che Mode and more! Most noted for being handpicked by Billy Idol to open f
	or the legendary 80s rocker\, they have also performed with Multi-Platinum
	 recording artist Tiffany\, Jane Wiedlin of The Go-Gos\, Clive Farrington 
	of When in Rome and Everclear. Featured on CNN and Good Morning America\, 
	Nite Wave has help raise over $17\,000 for Northwest Harvest and American 
	Red Cross\nThis event is 21 and over. Any ticket holder unable to present 
	valid identification indicating that they are at least 21 years of age wil
	l not be admitted to this event\, and will not be eligible for a refund. A
	ll sales are final. There are no refunds unless the event is cancelled or 
	postponed Opening Acts are subject to change or cancelation at any time wi
	thout notice. No refund will be owed if an Opening Act is changed or cance
	led. Doors times subject to change Tickets may not be resold or offered fo
	r resale. If we suspect tickets have been purchased for resale purposes on
	ly\, we reserve the right to void or cancel the tickets without refund. Ti
	ckets obtained from unauthorized sources may be invalid\, lost\, stolen or
	 counterfeit and if so\, are void.\nPrice: $37.35 - $37.35\n\nFrom The Cro
	codile
URL:https://www.ticketweb.com/event/nite-wave-performs-prince-the-crocodile
	-tickets/14012584
LOCATION:The Crocodile\, 2505 1st Ave\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
