SUMMARY:39th Annual Alumni Awards
DTSTAMP:20260214T003618Z
DTSTART:20260228T011500Z
DESCRIPTION:Join the Seattle University community on Friday\, February 27\,
	 2026\, at Pigott Auditorium as we honor nine remarkable individuals. Thes
	e awardees embody exceptional leadership\, service to the university and c
	ommunity\, academic excellence\, a commitment to care\, diversity\, and ju
	stice—all while upholding Seattle University's Jesuit values. Following th
	e ceremony\, we will enjoy hors d'oeuvres\, beverages and live music in th
	e PACCAR Atrium.\n\n \n\nRed Carpet: 5:15 p.m. | PACCAR Atrium\n\nAwards P
	resentation: 6 p.m. | Pigott Auditorium\n\nReception: 7 p.m. | PACCAR Atri
	um\n\n  \n\nAWARDEES\n\nALUMNUS OF THE YEAR \n\nDr. Norward Brooks\, '71 M
	BA\n\nAlbers School of Business Economics\n\n \n\nOUTSTANDING RECENT ALUMN
	A \n\nKatrina Phiri\, ’17 MBA \n\nAlbers School of Business and Economics 
	 \n\n \n\nUNIVERSITY SERVICE \n\nAnne Hotz Moran\, ’87 \n\nCollege of Arts
	 and Sciences \n\n \n\nPROFESSIONAL ACHIEVEMENT \n\nMadeline Haydon\, ’05 
	MBA\n\nAlbers Schools of Business and Economics \n\n \n\nCOMMUNITY SERVICE
	 \n\nTina O’Brien\, ’89\, ’98 MNPL \n\nCollege of Arts and Sciences \n\n \
	n\nJESUIT MISSION AWARD \n\nDr. Sonya Quitslund\, ’58 \n\nCollege of Arts 
	and Sciences \n\n \n\nATHLETICS HALL OF FAME \n\nPete Fewing \n\nHead Coac
	h\, SU Men’s Soccer \n\n \n\nATHLETICS HALL OF FAME \n\nAndre Lang\, ’95\,
	 ’04 JD \n\nMen’s Basketball \n\nCollege of Arts and Sciences\, School of 
	Law \n\n \n\nATHLETICS HALL OF FAME \n\nBlaise Wittenauer-Lee\, ’17 \n\nWo
	men’s Swimming \n\nCollege of Arts and Sciences\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Arts & 
	Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/39th-annual-alumni-awards
	/17717210/2026-02-27T00
LOCATION:Pigott Building\, Pigott Auditorium\, Seattle\, WA
